                    "verdict": "malicious",
                    "category": "code_insight",
                    "source": "palm",
                    "analysis": "The binary is ransomware. It enumerates local drives (`GetLogicalDrives`) and network shares (`WNetEnumResourceW`), then encrypts user files using the Windows CryptoAPI (`CryptEncrypt`). For efficiency, it uses a multi-threaded design with I/O Completion Ports. Post-encryption, it changes the desktop wallpaper (`SystemParametersInfoW` with `SPI_SETDESKWALLPAPER`), a common method to display a ransom note. A highly indicative PDB path, `D:\\Arena\\Cryptor_AES-RSA_V13\\Release\\Encoder.pdb`, confirms its purpose. It also checks the system language to avoid execution on Russian-language systems.",
                    "id": "bea90d10b000658691cdc6c334239d90e365f99e514ace07f05cd99a9e25fbb4-file-palm"
